thread.title: High school football roundup

author: Staff
title: High school football roundup
text:
Back Photo: 1 of 2 Next Graham Martin For the Times-Union Creekside's Chris Edwards tackles Fleming Island's Farell Turner on Friday at Creekside. Back Photo: 2 of 2 Next Daron.Dean@StAugustine.com Ponte Vedra quarterback Nick Tronti drops back for a pass Friday against Bishop Kenny. 
CLAY 56 
RIDGEVIEW 35 
Bilal Ally rushed for a county-record 450 yards and six touchdowns, in addition to a kickoff return score, as the Blue Devils ran wild against Ridgeview (1-6, 0-3 District 5-5A). ... Ally, a senior, has rushed for 846 yards in the last two weeks. ... Ridgeview’s Rhodeo Grey caught three TD passes. ... Colin Wilson added a rushing TD and an interception for Clay (4-3, 3-0). 
FORT WHITE 44 
UNION COUNTY 41 
Don Robinson scored the game-winning 41-yard touchdown on a pass from Demetric Jackson Jr. as the Indians roared back from a 14-point fourth-quarter hole against the Fightin’ Tigers (6-1, 2-1 District 6-1A). ... Ty Cook threw four TD passes, including a late 16-yarder to Manny Sykes that gave Union County a late lead. ... Robinson and Jacquez Pelham rushed for two TDs each to key the comeback for Fort White (5-2, 3-0). 
TRINITY CHRISTIAN 51 
DUVAL CHARTER 6 
Jalin Buie, Daequantae Showers and Rasheed Martin scored touchdowns as the top-ranked Conquerors overwhelmed Duval Charter (0-7, 0-2 District 2-3A)... Sophomore DB Tyreke Johnson returned a interception 65 yards for a TD, his second of the season. ... Billy Cobb connected on TD passes to J.C. Flowers and Derrick Smith as Trinity Christian (7-0, 2-0) remained perfect. 
HILLIARD 14 
BALDWIN 12 
Two missed conversions made the difference as the Red Flashes held off Baldwin (2-5, 0-3) in District 6-1A. ... A 6-yard TD pass from Landon Howard to Armani Scott put Hilliard (3-4, 1-3) ahead in the third quarter. ... Hunter Dozier’s 87-yard touchdown pass to Branden Williams brought Baldwin close, but the two-point conversion failed. 
BUCHHOLZ 35 
BARTRAM TRAIL 28 
Jackson White’s 15-yard TD pass to Luke Whittemore with 24.2 seconds left gave the Bobcats a comeback victory over the visiting Bears (5-3, 2-1 in District 3-7A). An 11-yard scoring pass from Joey Gatewood to Connor Aston in the fourth quarter put Bartram Trail ahead 28-27, but Buchholz (6-1, 2-0) came roaring back. ... The Bears face Oakleaf on Oct. 30 with a playoff spot at stake. ... Gatewood (8-of-12, 110 yards 2 TDs) and Jordan Smith (12-of-24, 133 yards, 2 TDs) led Bartram Trail. 
FLEMING ISLAND 23 
CREEKSIDE (OT) 17 
Fleming senior RB Trey Sneed rushed for 161 yards and the decisive TD in overtime as the Golden Eagles beat Creekside in a District 3-7A game. Fleming Island (1-2, 4-3) rallied from a 17-7 deficit in the third quarter. Creekside (0-2, 0-7) lost its 10th consecutive contest and had two chances late to win, but missed two long field goals in the last six minutes. ... Sneed’s 10-yard run on the first play of overtime gave Fleming Island the 23-17 lead, but left-footed place-kicker Hakeem Reid — who kicked a 45-yard field goal early in the fourth quarter to tie the score at 17-17 — bounced his extra point off the left upright to give Creekside a chance to win. However, Creekside moved backward on its overtime possession from the 10-yard line as a fourth-down pass from the 22 was intercepted to end the game. Senior RB Blake Morgan rushed for 167 yards and a TD for Creekside. 
ENGLEWOOD 42 
WOLFSON 6 
Quarterback Kenneth Jefferson threw two TD passes, both to Jameel Padgett as the Rams routed Wolfson on Homecoming. Jefferson also had a 1-yard TD run. ... Morris Little returned an interception 67 yards for Englewood (5-2). Wolfson fell to 0-8. 
NEASE 39 
MIDDLEBURG 17 
Leighton Alley passed for 285 yards and three TDs as the Panthers (5-2, 2-0 in District 4-6A) routed the host Broncos (0-8, 0-3). Ashton Wood had 164 yards and a pair of TDs on 10 catches, while Nate McClintock had a pair of rushing TDs. 
SUWANNEE 29 
RIBAULT 18 
Senior Aaron McAlister scored four TDs and rushed for 169 yards on six carries, clinching the District 3-5A title for the Bulldogs (5-1, 3-0) against visiting Ribault. ... Mike McCray scored two TDs for the Trojans (4-4, 2-1), the latter on a 36-yard pass from Derias McGoogin that brought Ribault within four. ... Suwannee’s defense limited Ribault to 52 yards rushing. 
BOLLES 42 
ATLANTIC 0 
The Bulldogs (7-1) used a 28-point second quarter on the way to a rout of host Port Orange Atlantic (0-7). ... Bolles took advantage of special teams, recovering three loose kickoffs in the first half. 
PALATKA 30 
MENENDEZ 0 
Dontaeveone Evans rushed for three second-half scores, pulling the Panthers clear of visiting Menendez (3-4, 1-2 District 5-5A). ... James Campbell opened the scoring for Palatka (3-4, 2-1) with a 24-yard TD pass to Markell Rasher. ... Palatka’s Eron Carter and Robert Passmore forced turnovers as the Panthers held Menendez to 191 yards. 
COLUMBIA 27 
ATLANTIC COAST 16 
The host Tigers moved to 6-1 and 2-0 in District 2-7A with a victory over the Stingrays (4-4, 1-2). Atlantic Coast tried to recover from a 17-0 halftime deficit, but couldn’t overcome it. 
ST. JOSEPH 10 
JOHN PAUL II 7 
Atoning for two earlier misses, Carlos Sanchez booted a 18-yard field goal in the fourth quarter to keep the Flashes perfect against John Paul II (4-3). ... After the Panthers took the lead on Brian Woodend’s 11-yard pass to Matthew Cowdrey, Matthew Considine tied the score after halftime with a 1-yard sneak. ... Ja’Kobi Dasher led St. Joseph (7-0) with 72 rushing yards. 
ELSEWHERE 
Bradford (5-3, 2-1) surprised visiting Keystone Heights (5-2, 1-1) 28-14 in District 3-4A play. ... West Nassau (5-2, 1-1 District 2-4A) routed county rival Fernandina Beach (2-6, 1-2) 30-0. ... Oakleaf (6-1) scored six quick touchdowns and never looked back in a 42-3 rout of visiting Arlington Country Day (0-6). ... Eagle’s View (2-5, 1-2 District 2-2A) won 38-8 to keep visiting Harvest Community (0-7, 0-2) winless. ... St. Johns Country Day (1-6) lost 35-0 at Gainesville Oak Hall (6-1).
